<div class="comment" id="comment-47755015">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/nickjj">nickjj</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">One nice thing about tmux is it also supports include files in its config.<p>This lets you put your theme colors in a different file, such as `source-file &quot;~&#x2F;.config&#x2F;tmux&#x2F;theme.conf&quot;` and then your theme switching external script or tool can symlink a specific theme&#x27;s tmux file to that path.<p>That&#x27;s what I do in my dotfiles:<p><pre><code>    # Main tmux config
    https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;nickjj&#x2F;dotfiles&#x2F;blob&#x2F;master&#x2F;.config&#x2F;tmux&#x2F;tmux.conf

    # One of the theme files
    https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;nickjj&#x2F;dotfiles&#x2F;blob&#x2F;master&#x2F;themes&#x2F;tokyonight-moon&#x2F;tmux.conf
