  <div class="comment_text">My two favorite tmux QoL improvements are enabling seamless navigation between neovim and tmux (there are many plugins but i use this one <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;aserowy&#x2F;tmux.nvim" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;aserowy&#x2F;tmux.nvim</a>) and extrakto which lets you fuzzy select anything in the tmux buffer and insert into the cursor or copy it to the clipboard. (<a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;laktak&#x2F;extrakto" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;laktak&#x2F;extrakto</a>)</div>
  
